ommon connection in the problem of mimesis. As this book ultimately argues, artificially separating language and sensibility results in a failure to encounter affect, the relation to difference affect is said to name, and the experience of thinking affect is taken to provoke.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCritical theory. 0aLanguage and culture. 0aVoice (Philosophy). 4aCommunication : Communication. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Language.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849253740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438492537423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438492537/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles